Motion Duration (Murray)

Purpose

This script imports, summarizes, and shows basic visualizations of an individual’s session data.

Import

s_data <- readr::read_csv(params$this_csv_fn)
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(

## See spec(...) for full column specifications.
s1_clean <- s_data %>%
  mutate(., run = run_n + 1) %>%
  rename(., corr = correct,
         dur_s = FWHM)

s1_subset <- s1_clean %>%
  dplyr::select(.,
                run,
                trial_n,
                dur_s,
                corr,
                rt)

Visualize

s1_subset %>% ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = trial_n, y = dur_s) +
  facet_grid(. ~ run) +
  geom_smooth() +
  geom_point() +
  ggtitle("Motion temporal duration threshold data")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

Cumulative performance across runs

s1_subset <- s1_subset %>%
  dplyr::group_by(., run) %>%
  dplyr::arrange(., dur_s) %>%
  dplyr::mutate(., cum_sum = cumsum(corr),
                cum_p = cum_sum/n())

s1_subset %>% ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = dur_s, y = cum_p) +
  facet_grid(. ~ run) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE)  +
  ggtitle("Motion temporal duration threshold data")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'loess' and formula 'y ~ x'

s1_subset %>%
  ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = trial_n, y = rt) +
  facet_grid(. ~ run) + 
  geom_point()  +
  ggtitle("Motion temporal duration threshold data")

Speed/accuracy trade-off

s1_subset %>%
  ggplot(.) +
  aes(x = dur_s, y = rt) +
  facet_grid(. ~ run) + 
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth() +
  ggtitle("Contrast sensitivity data")
